The paper deals with the problem of computing Delaunay triangulations, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. The paper proposes a new approach based on the witness complex, which is a well-known tool in computational topology. Therefore, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the use of numerical operations, which suggests that it may be relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper discusses the quality of the output simplices, which may be of interest to researchers in cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
